<p>Can someone tell me what is wrong with this code? I am trying to return the largest numbers from four separate arrays.</p>  <pre><code>function largestOfFour(arr) {   var longList = [];   for (var i in arr){     var longest = 0;     for (var x=0; x&lt;i.length; x++){       if (i[x] &gt; longest){         longest=i[x];       }       longList.push(longest);     }   }   return longList; }  largestOfFour([[4, 5, 1, 3], [13, 27, 18, 26], [32, 35, 37, 39], [1000, 1001, 857, 1]]); </code></pre>  <p>EDIT: Lye Fish provided the answer below. Here is the new code:</p>  <pre><code>function largestOfFour(arr) {   return arr.map(Function.apply.bind(Math.max, Math)); }  largestOfFour([[4, 5, 1, 3], [13, 27, 18, 26], [32, 35, 37, 39], [1000, 1001, 857, 1]]); </code></pre>